"4:144:10" : {s: 4, a: 144, w: 10, r: "امن", t: "ٱلْمُؤْمِنِينَ", l: "مُؤْمِن", lc: 202, tl: "l-mu'minīna", lb: "বিশ্বাসী",e: "the believers", b: "বিশ্বাসী / মুমিনদের", i: "orang-orang mukmin", f: 78, rm: "become/feel safe/secure, state of security/safety, trust, become quiet/tranquil in heart/mind, become free of expectation of evil or free of an object of dislike/hatred, promise/assurance of security/safety, become trustful/faithful/confident, to believe/acknowledge it, manifestation of humility/submission."},
"4:144:11" : {s: 4, a: 144, w: 11, r: "رود", t: "أَتُرِيدُونَ", l: "أَرَادَ", lc: 139, tl: "aturīdūna", lb: "ইচ্ছা করা",e: "Do you wish", b: "তোমরা কি চাও", i: "apakah kamu ingin", f: 2, rm: "to seek, ask a thing gently, search (for food), go to and fro in a pasture, go round about. iradatun - will, free will. mirwad - axle of a pully. rawada - to long after, desire, seduce, entice, seduce against the will (with an) as in 12:126. yuridu - he wishes, intends. It is used as an auxiliary verb as in 18:77. The word iradah is used for power and capacity with reference to subjugation as well as to option and choice. ruwaidan - for a little while, go gently (according to some grammarians the word is a diminutive form of which verbal noun is not in use, it is used as sing. plu. f. m.)."},
